<h2>Language & Style</h2>

<h3>Formal over informal</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>✗ Informal</th>
            <th>✓ Formal</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>look at</td>
            <td>examine</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>think about</td>
            <td>consider</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>get / give</td>
            <td>obtain / provide</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>set up</td>
            <td>establish</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>a lot</td>
            <td>many / numerous</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Stronger wording</h3>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>✗ Weak</th>
            <th>✓ Strong</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>very important</td>
            <td>crucial</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>very good</td>
            <td>excellent / ideal</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>very bad</td>
            <td>poor / disastrous</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>very weak argument</td>
            <td>unconvincing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>very strong argument</td>
            <td>robust</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<Callout type="dont">
    <h3>Never use</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>Contractions:</strong> can't → cannot, it's → it is,
        they're → they are, you're → you are
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Colloquial:</strong> cool, basically, literally, just,
        really
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Stance adjuncts:</strong> obviously, naturally, of course,
        undoubtedly
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Clichés:</strong> at the end of the day, think outside the
        box
    </p>
    <p><strong>Shortened:</strong> info, asap, telly</p>
</Callout>
